Core regression: request with X-Gateway-User-Id but wrong (or missing) signature must not be authenticated as that user. Bug currently returns User(id=gateway_uid) regardless of verify result, so test that sends bad signature and asserts rejection will fail on buggy code and pass after fix.

Test should cover four forgery paths so future refactors can't silently reintroduce any of them: bad signature, missing signature, legacy X-User-Id header alone, and Gateway-User-Id with no signature header at all. Each must raise Unauthorized (or equivalent), never return a User object.

```python
import pytest
from app.middleware.auth import AuthMiddleware, Unauthorized

SECRET = b"test-gateway-secret"

@pytest.fixture
def mw():
    return AuthMiddleware(secret=SECRET, sessions={})

def _req(headers=None, cookies=None):
    class R: pass
    r = R()
    r.headers = headers or {}
    r.cookies = cookies or {}
    return r

def test_invalid_signature_is_rejected(mw):
    req = _req(headers={
        "X-Gateway-User-Id": "42",
        "X-Gateway-Signature": "deadbeef",  # not a valid HMAC
    })
    with pytest.raises(Unauthorized):
        mw.resolve_user(req)

def test_missing_signature_is_rejected(mw):
    req = _req(headers={"X-Gateway-User-Id": "42"})
    with pytest.raises(Unauthorized):
        mw.resolve_user(req)

def test_legacy_x_user_id_header_is_rejected(mw):
    req = _req(headers={"X-User-Id": "42"})
    with pytest.raises(Unauthorized):
        mw.resolve_user(req)

def test_valid_signature_authenticates(mw):
    import hmac, hashlib
    uid = "42"
    sig = hmac.new(SECRET, uid.encode(), hashlib.sha256).hexdigest()
    req = _req(headers={
        "X-Gateway-User-Id": uid,
        "X-Gateway-Signature": sig,
    })
    user = mw.resolve_user(req)
    assert user.id == "42"

def test_signature_bound_to_uid_not_swappable(mw):
    # signature for uid=1 must not authenticate uid=2
    import hmac, hashlib
    sig_for_1 = hmac.new(SECRET, b"1", hashlib.sha256).hexdigest()
    req = _req(headers={
        "X-Gateway-User-Id": "2",
        "X-Gateway-Signature": sig_for_1,
    })
    with pytest.raises(Unauthorized):
        mw.resolve_user(req)
```

First three tests are what fails on current buggy diff — they document "forgery must raise" contract. Fourth test pins positive path so fix doesn't over-reject. Fifth test catches subtle bug where _verify checks signature validity in isolation but not binding to claimed uid (e.g. compares against any-valid signature).

Extra paranoia worth adding once base tests pass: replay test (same valid signed header reused after a ttl window must fail once timestamp binding lands), and returns-None test (assert middleware never returns None on failure — only raises — to pin the "fail closed" contract).
